President Barack Obama is set to travel to the Cleveland, Ohio area on Thursday, July 23, 2009. He will be touring the Cleveland Clinic and holding a town hall meeting on health reform at Shaker Heights High School. The town hall meeting will be open to the press, while the tour of the Cleveland Clinic will be closed to the press. Members of the public who wish to attend the town hall can register on a website or leave a voice message indicating their interest. The arrival and departure of Air Force One will be open to the press but closed to the public. Media coverage of the event is allowed, but RSVP is required. Detailed logistics and access information for media coverage are provided in the article.